social_posts.post_text: The most memorable week of my life! Thank you to everyone who made this trip to Taiwan so special. It’s still hard to believe that this is my actual life and not some crazy post Ironman fever dream. And yeah, @kristianblu is not the best karaoke singer :S

First camp of 2023! Trying out a new place after many years at the same locations. First impression of Morocco is extremely good! Will definitely have a good time here ;) 

Photos: @rojferman
Let’s see if more is more. Doing a camp at 2620m altitude. It’s a bit risky going this high, but always fun to try new stuff and keep things fresh #hemoglobin #hemogoblin #goblinmode

How do you follow up a historic year filled with Ironman wins and world records? The answer for @gustav_iden and @kristianblu is clear: Set new goals.

Both are targeting the 2024 Olympics, and their road to Paris begins in Morocco. Join in as the Norwegian duo turns up the intensity with a high-altitude training camp on their Propel Advanced SL bikes.

Watch the “Road to Paris”, now live → Link in profile

🎥: @santarastudios

#UltimateSpeed #RideUnleashed

Thank you, London! That was crazy. I didn’t make it easy for myself with a penalty already before the race was on, but finishing 5th at the @superleaguetriathlon Arena Games was way better than expected! Especially when I did it the looong and brutal way with the repechage in the morning. Been struggling in training the last few months so I feel like this was the turning point. The Short Course Athlete is back ;)

WTCS Yokohama is now three weeks away and the prep is going well with a good brick session today! As you might have heard by now I’m not doing @professionaltriathletesorg Ibiza. Going all in on this short distance thing 🏎️ and Ibiza being the weekend before just makes it unrealistic to perform in a @worldtriathlon race many time zones away, unless you are @kristianblu :S hopefully some of the other guys will take responsibility and tire him out before his travel to Japan 🫡

Photo: @bodyrocketcc

It’s a different way of fuelling, because traditionally you fuel for what you think you can do. But now we fuel because we want to do more.

We recently sat down with @Maurten_official at their HQ for the latest film in the M.Talks series. Watch to find out how we fuel our training and racing. We chatted about some of our top tips for fueling in the right way with Maurten — to maximize the benefits from each session and help prevent you from burning out

Preparation is done, tomorrow we race :) Had an amazing time here in Japan with @kenji_nener and @kojitriathlon 🇯🇵a lot on the line in terms of Olympic points for me, but getting to the start line fit and healthy is always a good place to start. Now let’s see if I also have a strong finish 👍

Life is unfair, but I am one of the luckiest. I was born to the best parents, in the best country, in the best time to be alive. Even when my mother was diagnosed with cancer two years ago I felt somehow lucky. Lucky  because I have had the opportunity to truly love someone enough to feel as sad as I did. Today my mothers luck ran out. Our family was gathered around her as she peacefully passed away after a long, long battle against the cancer. I’m not feeling lucky at the moment. It has been really hard to try to live a high performance life and race around the world when the hardest battles have been fought at home. For now I’ll take some time off with the family. Don’t know when I will be back. Elsker deg, Mamma ❤️

My most emotional triathlon ever. Sat down after the finish line and cried for a really long time. Didn’t know I was capable of feeling all these things at the same time. Happy to make the front pack on the bike. Proud to actually just make it to the start line this time. Frustrated that I’m so far from where I want to be. Most of all I just had an all consuming feeling of sadness. I don’t even know how to put it into words at the moment. Hopefully I can learn to handle all the emotions soon. Right now I’m just a bit too tired. 

Also, I’m extremely grateful for the support from my friends, family, sponsors, competitors and fans. Would honestly not be bothered to be racing now if it wasn’t for all of you ❤️

The shoes that made me sign with @on_running are finally out! The On Cloudboom Echo 3 was the shoe we did all the testing on before Kona last year with some different personal modifications. It was such an important piece of equipment that I actually chanced my race tactics because of its extreme characteristics. Get yours now 🫡

Font Romeu camp done. My fitness is getting better, but honestly I have no expectations to perform with the top dogs in @professionaltriathletesorg PTO Asian Open Singapore. Still looking forward to race and explore a new place. My schedule was changed after I was deemed “not good enough” to race the Paris Test Event after spending the first part of the season getting enough points to be on the start list. I made the start list, which in my opinion is “good enough”, but that is how things are sometimes. Anyway, will do the bike fam in Paris before I head over to Singapore Wednesday. 

📸: @talbotcox

Its sad to announce that my season is over. Struggled a bit with my Achilles last few weeks. Together with my doctor and coach we decided to end the season here. I honestly feel relieved in a way. This year has been one test after the other, and I feel like I have failed them all. No matter what I did 2023 would never be a good one. To get injured was just the last failed test that ended this season once and for all. 

Will be spending some of my time off in Nice at the launch of a short movie/anime made by @on called TriKings staring @kristianblu and myself. It’s a shame to go to Nice and not race, but I will be back at the start line where I belong when the time is right.

Everybody is working hard, but it takes a lot of courage to win the @ironmantri World Championship. To attack the course like @samlaidlow did, especially after a challenging season is truly insane. A champion in all aspects of the word. Looking forward to battle him and the rest of the guys next year :) 

Very motivated to get back to it now, but courageous enough to keep the off-season going for a bit longer 🏍️🏍️

You heard the whispers, now hear the ROAR.
 
As we step into the new year, PLASMAIDE is thrilled to announce a groundbreaking partnership with the powerhouse sports incubator company @santaratechnology 
 
Not only does our partnership with Santara Tech bring together two brands that are rooted in science and real-world performance, Santara Tech has taken an investment position in PLASMAIDE that underscores their commitment to the global success of the brand. 
 
Together, we’re integrating PLASMAIDE into the routines of Olympic and Ironman World Champions @kristianblu and @gustav_iden , supporting their training and competition efforts. For the past year, we’ve been working together to make this happen.
 
And that’s not all—our partnership with Santara Tech is set to redefine sports innovation. Through this one-of-a-kind sports incubator with unprecedented access and insight from the world’s leading athletes, coaches, and sports scientists we will together showcase the science-backed benefits of PLASMAIDE.
 
Here’s to pushing the boundaries of human endurance with science and passion.
